Heya - not sure I’ll be able to attend the coming quant call, so just in case here’s my feedback. I already gave a general feedback last time, so it’s just about 2 things here.
1. a minor UI adjustment: give the focus to the praise id field when opening the duplicate dialog, so that one doesn’t have to move the pointer there

2. when dealing with a lot of praises (+100), it’s hard to maintain consistency. I know when I scored an equivalent praise a bit before, but I can’t remember the exact score, so I might be inconsistent as a quantifier, even on a single session (even more so on multiple sessions).
One solution that came to my mind would be to let me, as a user, define my own qualitative scores. For instance:

“3”: some value added on a meeting
“5”: big value added on a meeting
“5”: 1 on 1 support
“8”: being great at leading an activity
“8 to 13”: some contribution to producing content, design, software
“21 to 35”: prominent contribution to content, design, software
etc
The above is totally subjective, at least for now. It’s heuristics that gradually emerge while scoring and that make it faster to score new praises and easier to maintain consistency.

It may enough to display it on an external window while quantifying. But maybe it could be useful to embed it in the quantifying app UI (in the future, it could even be used to score faster by clicking on options in the template, or to compare how quantifiers interpret praises).
